gn="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallux</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 align= BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/13/01 6:32:19 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.optushome.com.au/mlorant/galluxdamazar.gif WIDTH=96 HEIGHT=188 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Compare/Contrast between Scaled Knights and Shining (ins</span><hr size=1> There are 2 types of Paladins.<br>
<br>
There are those that believe in HP and there are those that believe in Wisdom.<br>
<br>
When you are facing AE mobs what is the point of being the last man standing? If everyone else is dead and you have 500 HP then that HP is wasted. No Paladin will ever be tanking on a raid anyway.<br>
<br>
Thats why I choose wisdom. A small increase in wisdom goes much further than the same amount of stamina. 19 wisdom = 228 mana. Thats enough for a Celestial Clensing. So you can equate 19 wisdom = 700 hp.<br>
<br>
How much HP does each stamina point add? Im not sure of how much but let me use 1 stamina = 6 HP. 39 stamina = 234 HP.<br>
<br>
Which would you prefer? Extra 234 HP or a quick tab and a Celestial Clensing for 700 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Imho a Paladin should aim for high AC with 200 wisdom. Thats my &quot;end game&quot; goal. I can do so much more with my mana instead of those that choose to increase their HP.<br>
<br>
I think Shining armour is a better armour set than Scaled Knights. The only thing I really prefer with Scaled Knight is it looks much better than Shining on humans <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Even if you dont think wisdom is important now, with the addition of our new Wave spell in Luclin, there will be nearly no excuse not to go for wisdom. Paladins are going to in serious demands on AE mobs and we are going to need all the mana we can get.<br>
